Purpose

Evolution Cycle 1 established the first stable architectural foundation of the KYBBA Framework.

The primary objective of this cycle was to define and validate the Structural Roles of every Entity Type Category, identify their unique System Capacities, and establish a consistent architectural basis for future framework development.

Rather than immediately decomposing categories into individual entities, this cycle prioritized understanding the structural contribution of each category to the operation of a Location.

---

Scope

The following components were completed during this Evolution Cycle:

- Entity Type Categories
- Structural Roles
- System Capacities
- Architectural Insights
- Emergent Patterns
- Design Principles
- Candidate Principles
- Framework Evolution Log (FEL)

The following stages remain outside the scope of this cycle:

- Entity Dependency Architecture
- Individual Entity Types
- Flows
- Response Layer
- System Evaluation

---

Major Discoveries

During this Evolution Cycle, several significant architectural discoveries emerged:

- Structural Roles provide the architectural basis for validating Entity Type Categories.
- Every Entity Type Category contributes one unique System Capacity.
- System Capacities form the bridge between framework Design and Architecture.
- Entity Type Categories naturally exhibit interdependence rather than strict hierarchy.
- Architectural functions emerge through the progression:
  - Entity
  - Capacity
  - Function
- Framework architecture should emerge through structured discovery rather than predetermined assumptions.

